    "daily_lesson": {
      "term": "Momentum Investing",
      "explanation_en": "Momentum investing is a strategy that targets stocks showing strong recent price trends and bullish technical signals \u2014 such as RSI in the 55\u201370 'sweet spot' and MACD crossovers \u2014 betting that assets already moving up tend to keep climbing in the short term. Today's top screener candidates like AAOI, HIMX, and APPF all score 95 because every key signal is aligned: RSI in bullish range (not yet overbought), MACD above its signal line, and price above the 20-day moving average. Risk-on days like today are when momentum strategies typically shine, as rising confidence pushes trending stocks further.",
